item.title:
New physics search via angular distribution of $  ar{B} 	o D^* (	o D \pi) 	au (	o \ell 
u_	au  ar{
u}_\ell)  ar{
u}_	au$ decays

item.description:
arXiv:2411.09414v1 Announce Type: new Abstract: The study of $ ar{B} 	o D^* 	au { ar{
u}}_	au$ angular distribution can be used to get information about new physics, which has been motivated by the presence of various $B$ anomalies. However, the inability to measure precisely the three-momentum of tau hinders this process, as the tau decay contains one or more undetected neutrinos. In this work, we present a measurable angular distribution of $ ar{B} 	o D^* 	au { ar{
u}}_	au$ by considering the additional decay $	au 	o \ell 
u_	au  ar{
u}_\ell$, where $\ell \in \{ e , \mu \}$. The full process used is $ ar{B} 	o D^* (	o D \pi) 	au (	o \ell 
u_	au  ar{
u}_\ell)  ar{
u}_	au$, where only the $\ell$ and $D^*$ are reconstructed, and a fit to the experimental angular distribution of this process can be used to extract information on new physics parameters. To demonstrate, we generate simulated data for this process and perform a sensitivity study to obtain the expected statistical errors on new physics parameters from experiments in the near future. We obtained a sensitivity of the order of 5% for the right-handed current and around 6% for the tensor current. In addition, we use the recent lattice QCD data on $B 	o D^*$ form factors and obtain correlations between form factors and new physics parameters.
